Saylor, the world=E2=80=99s most articulate Bitcoin cheerleader, spoke at t=
he Economic Club of New York. As usual, he delivered a mesmerizing stem-win=
der. Every time I hear Saylor talk, I immediately feel like I=E2=80=99m mis=
sing out on the greatest business opportunity of all time, one that bests t=
he cotton gin, the printing press, and the internet. Saylor, an MIT graduat=
e, is that convincing.<br/><br/>Of course, he=E2=80=99s always talking his =
own book. Using nearly every trick on Wall Street, Saylor has spent more
than $28 billion of MicroStrategy capital to buy just under 500,000 Bitcoin=
s, more than double the U.S.=E2=80=99s stash, at an average price of about =
$62,400 per coin. Microstrategy=E2=80=99s Bitcoin is now worth $43 billion,=
 and the market value of the highly leveraged company itself is now $72 bil=
lion. (Reminder to subscribers: This is not investment advice.)</p></div>
