"margin:0;">Saylor seemed even more fired up than usual at the Economic Clu=
b. He=E2=80=99s basically of
the view that Trump=E2=80=99s road to Damascus conversion on the merits of =
Bitcoin is one of the seminal events of our time. Saylor recounted how on i=
nauguration day, Trump, the 47th president, personally bought $47 million w=
orth of Bitcoin. =E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s a certain signal here, right?=E2=
=80=9D Saylor said. Trump=E2=80=99s S.E.C. then dropped the government=E2=
=80=99s lawsuits, initiated under <strong>Biden</strong> S.E.C. chair <stro=
ng>Gary</strong> <strong>Gensler</strong>, against Kraken, Robinhood, Cumbe=
rland, OpenSea, and Bored
Apes, as well as the suit against Coinbase. =E2=80=9CWhat you see is the po=
licy of the Gensler administration, which was to sue everybody and shut eve=
rything down and close the capital markets, is completely undone,=E2=80=9D =
he explained.<br/><br/>Saylor claimed there=E2=80=99s a =E2=80=9Cnew consen=
sus=E2=80=9D in Washington, about which he could not be more enthusiastic. =
=E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s a libertarian administration that=E2=80=99s in fav=
or of low taxes, low government engagement, pro-innovation, freedom,=E2=80=
=9D he said. =E2=80=9CThey=E2=80=99re very pro-Bitcoin, they=E2=80=99re
pro-crypto, they=E2=80=99re pro-business, they=E2=80=99re anti-censorship. =
And you have a set of fairly ideologically driven reformers in every part o=
f government, and none of them are wallflowers. This is a much more powerfu=
l, much more motivated cabinet than you had in 2016, and I think this is th=
e most powerful agent of change in our life.=E2=80=9D This, he concluded, c=
ould only be viewed as =E2=80=9Cmassively bullish=E2=80=9D for Bitcoin.<br/=
><br/>Perhaps, although Bitcoin is actually down 15 percent in the last mon=
th, due to a
combination of lack of demand, uncertainty over the scope of Trump=E2=80=99=
s plans for the industry, and the old Wall Street adage to buy the rumor an=
d sell the news. (Also, =E2=80=9Cbudget-neutral=E2=80=9D strategies for bui=
lding the Strategic Bitcoin Reserve are probably not what the maximalists h=
ad in mind, preferring, I=E2=80=99m sure, some sort of debt-driven Bitcoin-=
buying extravaganza.) Nor has it helped that Trump (and even <strong>Melani=
a</strong>) used the occasion of his inauguration to create memecoins for h=
is own
grotesque benefit, further discrediting an industry badly in need of some g=
